    <title>PSA: Samsung’s Galaxy Buds 3 Pro have some very delicate ear tips</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="A hands-on product photo of Samsung’s Galaxy Buds 3 / Galaxy Buds 3 Pro." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/cnqTCq8K5BasYvYD0bT6k4DSCfU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73466048/DSCF8079.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Photo by Chris Welch / The Verge&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="WTTWwX"&gt;Samsung’s new Galaxy Buds 3 Pro &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/24195011/samsung-galaxy-buds-3-pro-hands-on-preview-features"&gt;underwent a major redesign&lt;/a&gt;, making them look much more like AirPods and any number of other stemmed earbuds. So far, my impressions have been quite positive — full review coming soon — but even before the earbuds are widely released on July 24th, early buyers have been running into a frustrating issue. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="kAE0So"&gt;Apparently, the ear tips are quite fragile and can be prone to breaking if you’re not careful. Reddit is already starting to light up with examples:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li id="0ULqfz"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/galaxybuds/comments/1e4o3av/how_are_you_supposed_to_remove_the_tips/"&gt;“How are you supposed to remove the tips?”&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li id="NPQW0j"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/galaxybuds/comments/1e4rfbq/rant_buds_3_pro_eartips/"&gt;“Rant: Buds 3 Pro Eartips”&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p id="xustwp"&gt;The Zuyoni Tech YouTube channel also &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XFN4qCiQCK0"&gt;fell victim to the issue&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;figure class="e-image"&gt;
        
      &lt;cite&gt;GIF: &lt;a class="ql-link" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XFN4qCiQCK0" target="_blank"&gt;Zuyoni Tech&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/cite&gt;
      &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;Not the ideal first impression.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p id="uyUQ5v"&gt;With the switch to an AirPods-like design, Samsung...&lt;/p&gt;
